        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32911",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bonaparte",
                        "name": "bonaparte",
                        "displayName": "Sudheer Satyanarayana",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Isn't the expected behaviour? \n\nWhy would you want to make the CAPTCHA optional anyway?\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bonaparte",
                        "name": "bonaparte",
                        "displayName": "Sudheer Satyanarayana",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-24T11:56:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-24T11:56:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32912",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "If I want to add it but keep it hidden when it's not yet required. (It's also set required in ZF quickstart although it doesn't seem to matter.)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-24T12:29:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-24T12:29:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32915",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "shouldn't you use setIgnore() then?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=freak",
                        "name": "freak",
                        "displayName": "Dolf Schimmel (Freeaqingme)",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-24T15:11:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-24T15:11:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32917",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "setIgnore() won't work either.\n\nIn my opinion captcha element is a form element like any other element, so why shouldn't the same options like required etc. do the same things in captcha. And if you have noticed, the required option is also used for captcha in the part of ZF quickstart where Zend_Form is introduced. Obviously it's meant that you can decide if captcha is required or not (meant to inherit the basic functionality of the Zend_Form_Element).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-24T16:48:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-24T16:48:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35378",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I tried to hide captcha by using clearDecorators() for captcha element. It didn't work, because ViewHelper decorators wasn't removed.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-10-18T05:18:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-10-18T05:18:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
